The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Kids killed in Waziristan bombing
                                                                                                               Kids killed in Waziristan bombing
                            
	Islamabad, April 4 (PTI): Seventeen people, including five children, were killed and over 30 were injured today after a suicide bomber detonated his explosive-laden vehicle in Miranshah, a town in North Waziristan.        
	His target was a security convoy which was on its way from Bannu to Miran Shah. The bomber detonated his vehicle after security forces fired on him in a crowded bazaar.        
	 Seventeen civilians, including five children, were killed immediately.         
	Missile attacks        
	A US drone fired three missiles today in the northwestern tribal region near the Afghan border, killing at least 13 people, including women and children. The drone fired the missiles at the home of a tribesman in a village.                                                                                                                                                                                     
